  "prompt": "What is considered having \"asthma\"?",
  "response": "Asthma is a chronic respiratory condition characterized by several key features:\n\n1. Symptoms:\n- Recurring episodes of wheezing\n- Chest tightness\n- Shortness of breath\n- Persistent cough, especially at night\n\n2. Diagnostic Criteria:\n- Reversible airway obstruction\n- Increased airway sensitivity/inflammation\n- Demonstrated response to bronchodilators\n- Lung function tests showing reduced airflow\n\n3. Confirming Diagnosis:\n- Spirometry tests measuring lung function\n- Peak flow meter measurements\n- Medical history and physical examination\n- Allergy tests (if allergic asthma is suspected)\n\n4. Types of Asthma:\n- Allergic asthma\n- Exercise-induced asthma\n- Occupational asthma\n- Nocturnal asthma\n- Childhood asthma\n\n5. Severity Levels:\n- Intermittent\n- Mild persistent\n- Moderate persistent\n- Severe persistent\n\nA formal diagnosis is typically made by a healthcare professional after comprehensive testing and evaluation of symptoms, lung function, and medical history.",
